      "span_text": "Such antiidiotypic networks have already been shown to be a promising therapeutic approach. 22 Antibody-dependent cellular cytotoxicity may result in direct tumor destruction, inducing tumor-antigen-specific T-cell responses, with host antitumor immunity occurring by the production of tumor-directed cytotoxic T-cells, antibodies, or both. 24 Ströhlein et al. showed that treatment with catumaxomab and the trAb ertumaxomab induced an increase in autologous tumor-reactive T-cells in five of nine patients with peritoneal carcinomatosis. 7 T-cell activation was also demonstrated by increased serum levels of soluble interleukin-2 receptor."
